Module it.polimi.ingsw.PSP034

Package it.polimi.ingsw.PSP034.messages.playPhase

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnswerAction
    Message from the client to the server that communicates the action chosen by the current player, in response to a RequestAction.
    AnswerBooleanChoice
    Message from the client to the server communicating a boolean answer of a player, in response to a RequestBooleanChoice.
    AnswerStart
    Message from the client to the server that communicates that a player's turn correctly started, in response to a RequestStart.
    InfoIsStarting
    Message from the server to the client that communicates that another player is starting his/her turn.
    NextStateInfo
    Represents the information relative to the game phase to be executed.
    PlayAnswer
    Answer from the client to the server, in response to a PlayRequest.
    PlayRequest
    Answer from the server to the client, during the play phase of a game.
    RequestAction
    Move or build message containing all the possible actions for both workers of a given player.
    RequestBooleanChoice
    Message from the server to the client that requests to the player a boolean choice.
    RequestEnd
    Message from the server to the client that communicate to a player the end of his/her turn.
    RequestStart
    Request form the server to the client that communicates to a player that he/she can start his/her turn.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    RequiredActions
    This enum represents al the possible action that can be required during a turn phase.
